We won't bother him.

79
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,800
When he gets dumped,
we'll cry together.

80
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,810
For the sake
of our friendship.

81
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:12,940
Gets dumped, you say...?

82
00:05:35,910 --> 00:05:39,330
She can't be as
good looking as he says.

83
00:05:39,330 --> 00:05:43,540
He tends to exaggerate, and
he easily convinces himself.

84
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:44,860
You're right.

85
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:48,200
I think it was when we
were in middle school...

86
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:51,430
We went to
Akina Lake to fish.

87
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:56,730
We didn't catch anything until I caught a small one just before we went home.

88
00:05:56,730 --> 00:05:59,000
He was so excited,
and said...

89
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,200
...``It's so big !''
out loud.

90
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:04,350
It was this small.

91
00:06:04,350 --> 00:06:07,800
Strangers came to see it.

92
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:10,750
I was so embarrassed
at that time.

93
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:15,370
Iketani can really
exaggerate things.

94
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:18,650
Kenji, take a look.

95
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:26,650
Damn, I was so absorbed in talking,
I wasn't paying attention to my right foot.

96
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:29,600
I was supposed to follow him,
but I caught up with him.

97
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:32,020
Sorry, Iketani !

98
00:06:32,020 --> 00:06:33,450
Forgive me.

99
00:06:33,450 --> 00:06:36,200
We just wanted to see
what Mako looks like.

100
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,850
It's true.

101
00:06:37,850 --> 00:06:40,680
We have no intention of bothering you on your date.

102
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,500
Don't be mad.

103
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:45,510
We'll turn around at
the next interchange.

104
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:48,200
It can't be helped.

105
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,150
You don't
have to leave.

106
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:53,280
I don't mind
introducing you to her.

107
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:54,310
Really ?

108
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:55,380
Great.

109
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:56,850
But...

110
00:06:56,850 --> 00:07:00,900
...don't follow us after
that, or I will get mad.

111
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:01,860
Okay.

112
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:04,100
So...

113
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:08,940
...they're my friends.

114
00:07:10,260 --> 00:07:12,780
Nice to meet you.
I'm Sato Mako.

115
00:07:18,970 --> 00:07:19,790
H...hi.

116
00:07:19,790 --> 00:07:21,280
H...hello.

117
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,700
Well, Mako...

118
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:24,550
Okay.

119
00:07:33,850 --> 00:07:36,300
Are we dogs
or something ?

120
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:46,890
It's not a dream.

121
00:07:46,890 --> 00:07:48,770
I don't believe it.

122
00:07:49,610 --> 00:07:51,850
I'm so shocked.

123
00:07:51,850 --> 00:07:54,390
How could Iketani
find such a cute girl ?

124
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:56,850
Road Racers don't
need a girl.

125
00:07:56,850 --> 00:07:59,300
Kenji, why don't
we cry together ?

126
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:00,850
What do you mean ?

127
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:03,240
Are you saying I'll
never find a girl ?

128
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:05,600
It was just a joke.

129
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:10,710
What should
we do now ?

130
00:08:10,710 --> 00:08:11,760
Well...

131
00:08:12,850 --> 00:08:18,900
Karuizawa isn't the place for three guys to hang out this time of year.

132
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:22,340
Why don't we go to
Usui's mountain pass ?

133
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,630
S...sorry.

134
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:45,000
Do you have a
favorite car, Mako ?

135
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,190
