my favorite...

136
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:53,500
...but I used to dream
of the previous model RX-7.

137
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,400
The FC ?

138
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,230
You have
good taste.

139
00:08:59,610 --> 00:09:02,730
You're a Road
Racer, aren't you ?

140
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:06,850
Well...can you tell ?

141
00:09:06,850 --> 00:09:11,110
I usually try to drive
like everyone else.

142
00:09:12,850 --> 00:09:18,830
What do you think
of Road Racers ?

143
00:09:19,510 --> 00:09:22,850
I think it's alright,
because I also like cars.

144
00:09:23,850 --> 00:09:24,900
Really ?

145
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:31,020
Road Racers are better at driving than ordinary people.

146
00:09:31,020 --> 00:09:34,200
If you have money, you
can buy a good car...

147
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,340
...but you can't
buy technique.

148
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:40,250
I prefer someone who can use
technique when needed...

149
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:45,090
...to someone who has
an expensive imported car.

150
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:47,650
She's great.

151
00:09:47,650 --> 00:09:49,700
She's my ideal girl.

152
00:09:56,780 --> 00:09:59,390
So this is
Usui's mountain pass...

153
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:04,950
This is the first time I've seen it, and it's a much harder winding road than I imagined.

154
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:07,750
It's incredible.

155
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:12,350
It's one corner after another,
and the road is narrow.

156
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:15,460
It's nothing like Akina.

157
00:10:17,470 --> 00:10:20,590
I wonder who's the
fastest on Usui.

158
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:26,800
Umm...you are...

159
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,200
Y...yes...?

160
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:31,500
From a man's
point of view...

161
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:36,850
...if there's a girl who likes mountain passes, and tries to be a Road Racer...

162
00:10:36,850 --> 00:10:38,400
...what would you
think about that ?

163
00:10:41,460 --> 00:10:42,960
Sil-Eighty ?

164
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:46,600
Yeah, the blue Sil-Eighty is said to be the fastest.

165
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,500
Don't be surprised
by this, though.

166
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,390
The driver
is a woman.

167
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:52,200
A woman ?!

168
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:55,630
Female Road Racer ?

169
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,320
Y...yeah.

170
00:10:57,320 --> 00:11:00,850
I like it.
I think it's okay.

171
00:11:00,850 --> 00:11:01,850
It's great.

172
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:05,040
A female Road Racer would
be wonderful to talk to.

173
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,000
Is that so ?

174
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,320
Yeah.

175
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:11,250
I see.
I get it.

176
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:14,000
She wants to be a Road Racer.

177
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,730
And her dream
car is the FC.

178
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:19,900
A girl driving
a Sil-Eighty...?

179
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:22,280
What's a Sil-Eighty ?

180
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,230
Is it an import ?

181
00:11:23,230 --> 00:11:24,850
No.

182
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:29,360
The Sil-Eighty is a 180
with a Silvia front {face} on it.

183
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:33,200
A Silvia and a 180 are combined,
so it's called a Sil-Eighty.

184
00:11:34,850 --> 00:11:40,150
And the driver is a girl, and she's the fastest on Usui's mountain pass.

185
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:42,100
I want to see this.

186
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:45,870
If you wait until nightfall, you'll be able to see it on Usui's mountain pass.

187
00:11:45,870 --> 00:11:51,490
But don't even think about challenging her, because none of the locals can defeat her.

188
00:12:09,110 --> 00:12:11,670
It's called the
Akina Speedstars.

189
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:17,450
I assembled the team, and we have the fastest driver on Akina.

190
00:12:17,450 --> 00:12:19,370
He's my junior worker.

191
00:12:19,370 --> 00:12:23,050
Speaking of the skill,
I guess I'd be second.

192
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,850
What's wrong, Mako ?

193
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:28,020
Oh, nothing at all.

194
00:12:28,020 --> 00:12:29,250
Sorry.

195
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:32,450
I must be boring you with
all this talk about cars.

196
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:34,850
No, not at all.

197
00:12:34,850 --> 00:12:38,430
I like cars a lot,
so it's fun.

198
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:40,490
Really ?
That's good.

199
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:49,130
Ah, do you think
drift is cool, too ?

200
00:12:49,130 --> 00:12:50,440
A little...

201
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:55,390
You have to drive hard
like me to master that.

202
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:56,960
It's a dangerous technique.

203
00:12:58,370 --> 00:13:01,150
Are you good
at drifting ?

204
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,320
A little...

205
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,950
I'm happy for some reason.

206
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:06,390
You are...?

207
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:16,990
Thank you.
It was fun today.

208
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:19,710
Ah, Mako...

209
00:13:19,710 --> 00:13:21,310
Yes ?

210
00:13:21,310 --> 00:13:24,550
Are you...
Well...

211
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,250
Is there someone you're
going out with now...?

212
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:29,250
Well...

213
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:31,400
Do you have anyone ?

214
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,930
I don't have a boyfriend.

215
00:13:37,740 --> 00:13:41,850
So, please call
me again, Iketani.

216
00:13:51,590 --> 00:13:54,110
Hey, Iketani...
Can you hear me ?

217
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:57,210
Iketani, get a grip.

218
00:14:00,330 --> 00:14:01,650
I'm...

219
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:04,260
Why're you
guys still here ?

220
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:08,220
We were concerned about you,
so we couldn't go home.

221
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:10,960
So how was it ?
Did it go well ?

222
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:15,610
Today is such
a wonderful day.

223
00:14:16,660 --> 00:14:18,500
Let's go eat.

224
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:20,500
It doesn't happen very often,
but it's gonna be my treat.

225
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:25,020
And it's not a bad idea to take a look at the Usui guys' driving, too.

226
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:28,390
I guess it
went well.

227
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:30,850
So miracles do happen.

228
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:36,850
Pretty good.

229
00:14:36,850 --> 00:14:39,560
Everyone on Usui
is highly skilled.

230
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:44,300
Hey, Takumi...

231
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:47,850
...you'd never seen a mountain pass other than Akina, right ?

232
00:14:47,850 --> 00:14:49,010
How was it ?

233
00:14:49,010 --> 00:14:51,000
``How was it ?''

234
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:55,550
I wasn't driving,
so I don't know.

235
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:59,750
Are you sure ?
You looked so serious.

236
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:00,780
I did ?

237
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:03,850
Your eyes looked totally
different from now.

238
00:15:03,850 --> 00:15:05,900
I can't believe they're
of the same person.

239
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:07,700
What do you say ?
Do you think you can drive it ?

240
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:11,100
I can't tell
unless I try.

241
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,220
Here it comes !

242
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:13,450
The Sil-Eighty ?

243
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:24,700
Nonstop counter drift ?

244
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:26,220
What the hell ?

245
00:15:28,210 --> 00:15:30,100
She's really good.

246
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:31,870
See that ?

247
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:34,090
The road is narrow,
so it looked so exciting.

248
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:39,560
I talked big and told Mako
that I'm good at drifting...

249
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:43,990
...but in reality, I panic
when the rear starts to skid.

250
00:15:43,990 --> 00:15:45,850
This is bad.

251
00:15:45,850 --> 00:15:49,150
I've gotta practice hard,
or my angel will be gone.

252
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,260
Let's go down.

253
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:52,710
Okay.

254
00:15:52,710 --> 00:15:55,680
Every mountain pass has
an incredible driver.

255
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:12,110
Hey, look...Iketani
is driving so fast.

256
00:16:12,110 --> 00:16:15,840
There are three in here,
so I can't keep up.

257
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:18,200
You'd better
keep your distance.

258
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:23,380
The rhythm is bad.
Something's wrong with his car.

259
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:25,590
Do you think
something's gonna happen ?

260
00:16:25,590 --> 00:16:28,870
I don't mean that something
will happen, but probably...

261
00:16:28,870 --> 00:16:29,960
Probably ?

262
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:38,200
He screwed up, just
like you said.

263
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:40,900
Just like Takumi said.

264
00:16:43,660 --> 00:16:45,360
Oh shit, a car is coming !

265
00:16:54,910 --> 00:16:58,260
That was close.
Who's that idiot ?

266
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:02,850
The rear skidded, he got scared, released the gas pedal, and oversteered.

267
00:17:02,850 --> 00:17:04,850
That's the most uncool spin
only an amateur would do.

268
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:07,850
Hey, 13 dude !

269
00:17:07,850 --> 00:17:12,000
If you don't move your car quickly,
you'll endanger other cars !

270
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,510
I'm moving it now.

271
00:17:15,310 --> 00:17:17,380
It's so embarrassing !

272
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:19,960
How uncool.
Let's pretend to be strangers.

273
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:22,850
I'm really sor...

274
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:42,750
What's wrong ?

275
00:17:43,450 --> 00:17:45,190
It's nothing.

276
00:17:53,710 --> 00:17:59,290
Usui Mountain's fastest
driver is Mako in her Sil-Eighty.

277
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,770
I feel like
I could die.

278
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:08,530
He took the day off ?

279
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:10,510
He didn't even call.

280
00:18:10,510 --> 00:18:13,550
That workaholic, Iketani ?

281
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:15,200
I don't believe it.

282
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:18,230
He must've been
really shocked.

283
00:18:18,230 --> 00:18:21,870
He didn't talk
at all afterwards.

284
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:24,220
When we stopped at a service
area to use the restroom...

285
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:26,680
...he looked out of it,
and his eyes weren't focusing.

286
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:30,300
We were so sorry for him,
we didn't know what to say.

287
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:33,200
I had a bad feeling.

288
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:36,230
She's too cute to
be Iketani's girl.

289
00:18:36,230 --> 00:18:39,360
After all, Road Racers
don't need a girl.

290
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:43,350
Lonely driver, Itsuki.
That's my motto.

291
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:45,950
I hope the shock
doesn't last too long.

292
00:18:55,660 --> 00:18:58,130
Kouichiro, phone call !

293
00:18:58,780 --> 00:19:00,350
I don't want to take it.

294
00:19:00,350 --> 00:19:03,410
Tell him I'm sleeping.
It must be Kenji anyway.

295
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:05,250
It's a girl !

296
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:06,820
Sato Mako !

297
00:19:17,010 --> 00:19:19,830
You said you
wanted to talk.

298
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:24,780
If you're making
fun of me, please stop.

299
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:29,200
No, I'm not
making fun of you.

300
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:32,600
I never thought that you'd be the driver of that incredible car.

301
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:40,400
I saw your Sil-Eighty
drifting at full speed.

302
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:42,600
They say you're
the fastest on Usui.

303
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:48,380
If so, you could
have told me.

304
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:50,190
I'm sorry.

305
00:19:50,190 --> 00:19:53,800
I didn't mean
to lie to you.

306
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:55,820
It was shocking
for me, too.

307
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:59,930
And I thought I should
tell you the truth.

308
00:19:59,930 --> 00:20:01,400
Truth ?

309
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:07,480
I'm actually
the quiet type.

310
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:08,480
Quiet...?

311
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:12,930
That's hard to believe, because you can perform such a dynamic drift.

312
00:20:12,930 --> 00:20:17,400
You know how some people's personalities change once they get behind the wheel ?

313
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,660
I'm that type.

314
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:25,680
When I drive fast,
guys don't see me as a girl.

315
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:29,090
So I thought
I should quit.

316
00:20:29,090 --> 00:20:30,980
I've made up my mind.

317
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:34,970
I'm quitting road
racing this summer.

318
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:38,850
For my last memory
of this summer...

319
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:42,560
...would you let me race against Akina's Eight-Six on Usui's mountain pass ?

320
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:46,550
That's my wish.

321
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:50,880
If you make my
wish come true...

322
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:54,120
...you can have
my virginity.

323
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:58,420
Wait a minute.
Don't say such a thing.

324
00:20:58,420 --> 00:20:59,970
Am I not enough ?

325
00:20:59,970 --> 00:21:01,570
It's not that.

326
00:21:01,570 --> 00:21:06,200
He's my friend, so I can't
make a deal like that.

327
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:10,740
I understand.

328
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:15,760
Her target was never me,
it was always Takumi.

329
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:17,240
It's obvious.

330
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:21,940
Otherwise, a cute girl like her would never be interested in me.

331
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:30,370
Okay, I'll see
what I can do.

332
00:21:30,370 --> 00:21:31,340
Really ?

333
00:21:31,340 --> 00:21:33,900
Don't misunderstand me.

334
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:38,460
I'll cooperate, but not because
I want something from you.

335
00:21:38,460 --> 00:21:39,970
Iketani...

336
00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:44,130
I just want to make
your wish come true.

337
00:21:55,650 --> 00:21:57,200
It's alright.

338
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:03,200
Although it was only a short time,
I was seriously in love with Mako.

339
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:07,790
As long as she's happy,
I'll be satisfied.

340
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:21,220
People would call me a fool,
but I really loved her.

341
00:22:22,650 --> 00:22:26,500
Even though it was my misunderstanding, I really loved her.

